The paper proposes two deep models for engagement assessment using electroencephalograph (EEG) signals with scarce label information. This involves machine learning and human-computer interaction, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the use of EEG signals for engagement assessment suggests a potential application in cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
